guidebook.jurassicsaga.achillobator.desc: Achillobator meaning "Achilles hero" is a genus of large dromaeosaurid theropod dinosaur that lived during the Late Cretaceous period.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.alamosaurus.descr: Alamosaurus meaning "Ojo Alamo lizard" is a genus of titanosaurian sauropod dinosaurs containing a single known species, Alamosaurus sanjuanensis.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.apatosaurus.descr: Apatosaurus was a massive, long-necked Jurassic herbivore, moving in herds and feeding on low to mid-level vegetation.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.baryonyx.descript: Baryonyx is a genus of theropod dinosaur which lived in the Barremian stage of the Early Cretaceous period, about 130–125 million years ago. The first skeleton was discovered in 1983.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.brachiosaurus.des: A massive sauropod from the Late Jurassic, characterized by its long neck and upright posture. Unlike other sauropods, its forelimbs were longer than its hindlimbs, allowing it to reach high vegetation. It likely traveled in groups and required vast amounts of plant material daily.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.cearadactylus.des: A pterosaur from the Early Cretaceous of Brazil. It had a long, toothed beak and is believed to have fed on fish. With a wingspan of around 4–5 meters, it was a capable flyer that likely soared over coastal environments.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.click_prompt_goto: Click to go to the %s page.
Go to this creature's Information Page.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.coelurus.descript: Coelurus (/sɪˈljʊərəs/ si-LURE-əs) is a genus of coelurosaurian dinosaur from the Late Jurassic period.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.compsognathus.des: Compsognathus is a genus of small, bipedal, carnivorous theropod dinosaur. Members of its single species Compsognathus longipes could grow to around the size of a chicken.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.dilophosaurus.des: A medium-sized theropod from the Early Jurassic period. It had a pair of distinctive crests on its head, likely used for display. It may have been a scavenger or opportunistic predator. Contrary to some depictions, there is no evidence of venom or a frill.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.dryosaurus.descri: Dryosaurus was an iguanodontid ornithopod dinosaur. They lived during in the Late Jurassic period. Its name meaning "Oak lizard"
guidebook.jurassicsaga.euoplocephalus.de: Euoplocephalus is a genus of large herbivorous ankylosaurid dinosaurs, living during the Late Cretaceous of Canada. It has only one named species, Euoplocephalus tutus.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.gallimimus.descri: A fast, ostrich-like dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous of Mongolia. It had long legs adapted for speed and a beak with no teeth, suggesting an omnivorous diet. Fossils show it may have moved in groups, potentially for protection or migration.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.hadrosaurus.descr: A duck-billed herbivore from the Late Cretaceous period of North America. Known for its strong hind legs and a flattened, broad snout, Hadrosaurus likely moved in herds and used vocalizations for communication.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.home:
Welcome to Jurassic Saga Alphas! Please keep in mind that this is an alpha version of the mod, thus is filled with bugs (not Mosquitos!). Report your bugs in our official Discord Server! 
This guidebook is still work in progress, so any information is subject to change! 
Right click a mob with this item to inspect it.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.ludodactylus.desc: Ludodactylus (meaning "play finger") is a genus of anhanguerid pterodactyloid pterosaur from the Early Cretaceous period.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.maiasaura.descrip: Maiasaura, a hadrosaurid genus, famous as a "good mother lizard," as fossils show it cared for its young. Maiasaura also were light weight for their size and could run.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.meganeura.descrip: A giant predatory insect from the Carboniferous period with a wingspan of up to 70 cm. It resembled a modern dragonfly but lived in a high-oxygen atmosphere that allowed insects to grow much larger than today.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.mesolimulus.descr: An ancient genus of horseshoe crab dating back to the Jurassic. It resembled modern horseshoe crabs and is an example of evolutionary stability. These creatures lived in shallow marine environments and fed on small invertebrates.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.metriacanthosauru: Metriacanthosaurus meaning "moderately-spined lizard" is a genus of metriacanthosaurid dinosaur from the Oxford Clay Formation of England, dating to the Late Jurassic period, about 160 million years ago (lower Oxfordian).
guidebook.jurassicsaga.microceratus.desc: Microceratus (meaning "small-horned") is a dubious genus of small ceratopsian dinosaur that lived in the Cretaceous period of Mongolia. It walked on two legs, had short front arms, a characteristic ceratopsian frill and beak-like mouth.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.othnielia.descrip: Othnielia is a genus of Hypsilophodontid dinosaur featured in Jurassic Park (1992). It is featured in the Hypsilophodontid Highlands enclosure on the safari drive.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.parasaurolophus.d: A herbivorous dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous with a distinctive long, backward-curving crest. The crest may have been used for visual display, sound resonance, or thermoregulation. It likely lived in herds and fed on vegetation.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.proceratosaurus.d: Proceratosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived during the Middle Jurassic in what is now England. The holotype and only known specimen consists of a mostly complete skull with an accompanying lower jaw and a hyoid bone, found near Minchinhampton, a town in Gloucestershire.
A small, lightly built dinosaur from the Late Triassic of Europe. It was a fast runner and likely insectivorous or carnivorous, feeding on small vertebrates. Its size and speed made it effective at darting through underbrush.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.stegosaurus.descr: Stegosaurus stenops was a large, plated herbivore with a small head, spiked tail, and distinctive double row of back plates.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.styracosaurus.des: Styracosaurus is an extinct genus of herbivorous ceratopsian dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous. It had four to six long parietal spikes extending from its neck frill, a smaller jugal horn on each of its cheeks.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.triceratops.descr: Triceratops is an extinct genus of herbivorous chasmosaurine ceratopsid dinosaur that lived in North America during the very end of the Cretaceous period.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.troodon.descripti: A small theropod from the Late Cretaceous with one of the largest brain-to-body ratios among dinosaurs. It had keen senses, grasping hands, and serrated teeth, suggesting it was an intelligent and adaptable predator or omnivore.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.tutorial1_left:
How to clone your first creature: 
Mine fossils underground and analyze them using a Genetic Analyzer to gain DNA coins. Then, combine those DNA coins with the same (or donor) DNA in the DNA Modifier. 
Once you have a 100% DNA Coin, combine it with a syringe and a suitable unfertilized egg in the crafting table to create a Fertilized Egg.
To unfertilize an egg, put it in the crafting table along with a syringe.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.tutorial1_right:
You can now incubate your fertilized eggs in the Incubator, then use them on the ground to hatch your first little Creature! 
Not satisfied? why not try to extract some Genes from 100% DNA samples and put them on your creature DNA via the DNA Modifier?
guidebook.jurassicsaga.tylosaurus.descri: A large marine reptile from the Late Cretaceous, part of the mosasaur family. It could reach over 14 meters in length and was a top predator in its environment, feeding on fish, other marine reptiles, and even smaller mosasaurs.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.tyrannosaurus.des: Tyrannosaurus (meaning "tyrant lizard") is an extinct genus of tyrannosaurid theropod dinosaur that lived in North America during the Late Cretaceous period around 73-66 million years ago.
guidebook.jurassicsaga.velociraptor.desc: A small, agile predator from the Late Cretaceous of Mongolia. It measured around 2 meters in length and was covered in feathers. It had a sickle-shaped claw on each foot and likely hunted small animals or scavenged.
